  "text": "One who cuts a vegetable into [very] fine pieces in order to cook them has transgressed a subcategory of Grinding and is liable. Therefore, it is forbidden to shred hay or carob before animals, whether large animals or small animals, because it appears as if one is [transgressing] Grinding. However, one may cut gourds before an animal, or an animal carcass before dogs, because there is no [prohibition] of grinding regarding fruit. One may untie bundles of straw before an animal or spread, by hand, small sheaves, but not large sheaves, because of the effort it entails.",
